What is a stack?
A stack is a linear data sructure. It follows the LIFO(Last in first out). Insertions and deletions are done at only one end of the stack. A stack consists of a top.
When the stack it empty the value of top = -1.
There are 3 operations allowed in a stack
1.push - to insert an element in the stack.
2.pop- to remove an element in the stack.
3.peek- displaying the contents of stack.
All the elements in the stack are pushed and popped from one end only i.e. top.
